  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: working tree clean, branch `work/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1`, baseline build passes, task 030 ✅. Load knowledge. Declare RIGOR LEVEL: FULL.</step>
    <step order="1">Read design §5 "Approval queue" + §11 anti-patterns. Confirm the opt-in semantics: `Action.governance.autoApprove == true` is the gate; this resolver verifies + audits, NEVER silently approves.</step>
    <step order="2">Create `AutoApproveGateResolver.cs` — ctor injects `IActionRegistryService` (to lookup Action.governance), `IAuditService`, `ILogger`. `ResolveAsync`:
      (a) load Action via `actionRunId.ActionId`,
      (b) if `Action.governance.autoApprove != true`, throw `InvalidOperationException("Auto-approve invoked for Action that did not opt in")` with structured log,
      (c) audit `LogGateDecision(GateDecision.Approved, reason: "auto-approve per Action.governance.autoApprove=true")`,
      (d) return `new GateOutcome(GateDecision.Approved, DateTime.UtcNow, ResolvedByUserId: null, Reason: "auto-approve", ApprovalRecordId: null)`.</step>
    <step order="3">Register DI in `AddGatesFeature()`: `services.AddScoped&lt;AutoApproveGateResolver&gt;();` — NOT keyed (since Action Definitions opt-in by name override, not by GateType). Document the orchestrator's by-name resolver lookup in `notes/decisions/034-resolver-name-lookup.md` (this becomes the contract Phase 4 task 042 implements).</step>
    <step order="4">Write unit tests:
      (a) `ResolveAsync_OptedIn_ReturnsApproved` — Action with `governance.autoApprove=true` returns Approved + audits.
      (b) `ResolveAsync_NotOptedIn_Throws` — Action with `governance.autoApprove=false` (or unset) throws `InvalidOperationException`.
      (c) `ResolveAsync_NoActionFound_Throws` — `IActionRegistryService.GetActionAsync` returns null → throw with descriptive message.
      (d) `ResolveAsync_Audits_WithExpectedReason` — audit reason exactly matches `"auto-approve per Action.governance.autoApprove=true"`.
      (e) `ResolveAsync_AuditOrdering_AfterDecision` — audit called exactly once per outcome, AFTER decision computed (no double-audit).</step>
    <step order="5">Build + run tests: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` exits 0; `dotnet test` passes new tests. Measure publish-size delta; expect &lt; 0.05 MB. Record in `notes/measurements/034-publish-size-delta.md`.</step>
    <step order="6">Verify ADR-010 DI budget across `AddActionEngineModule()` after this task. Total Phase 3 registrations should be roughly: 030 contract (0 concrete), 031 (3 keyed), 032 (3: channel singleton + resolver keyed + endpoint), 033 (3: HttpClient + validator + resolver keyed), 034 (1: scoped) — ≈10 of 15 budget. Document running tally in `notes/measurements/phase3-di-budget.md`.</step>
    <step order="9.5">Run quality gates: `code-review` (focus: opt-in verification correctness, no silent-approval failure modes, audit-after-decision ordering), `adr-check` (ADR-001/008/010/013/015/029). Mandatory review per CLAUDE.md §6 — this resolver bypasses a security guardrail by design; verify the opt-in path is airtight.</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: 034 ✅. Update `current-task.md`. After all of Group D (031–034) ✅, task 035 unblocks.</step>
    <step order="11">Commit + push. Document any deviations or contract refinements.</step>
  </steps>

