  <notes>
    Tiny class, big responsibility — auto-approve bypasses the human-gate guardrail. The TWO independent checks (orchestrator routes by name + resolver verifies opt-in) form defense-in-depth. Removing either is a regression.

    The `Reason` field on the audit MUST be exactly `"auto-approve per Action.governance.autoApprove=true"` — admins can grep audit logs for this signature to enumerate which Actions auto-approved historically. Changing the string breaks operational forensics.

    R2 consideration: a "soft auto-approve with timeout" variant could exist where the resolver waits N seconds for a human override before approving (e.g., "I'll auto-approve in 10 seconds unless you intervene"). Out of scope here; document as a future enhancement.
  </notes>

